<s> It is known that Jurakudai was once called " Uchino Okamai " ( or Uchino no Onkamae ) during construction , which first appears in " Tamon-in Nikki " ( The Diary of Tamon-in Temple ) , in the section of February 27 , 1586 , ' the construction of Uchino Okamai began on the last 21st . ' </s>
