<s> Amanohashidate has shrunk in recent years due to erosion , and is in danger of disappearing . </s>
<s> This is because dams were built on the rivers after the war , reducing the amount of sediment carried from the mountains to the sea , and destroying the balance of sediment deposits and erosion on Amanohashidate . </s>
<s> To prevent further erosion , the administration has installed many small erosion barriers on the sand bar in an attempt to stop the sand from washing away ( in the picture from the south ( Hiryukan ) , it is the part on the right where the beach is serrated ) . </s>
<s> At one time the trees were blighted by pine weevils , and were in danger of being wiped out . </s>
